---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { contactEmail } from '../config/site';

const siteOrigin = Astro.site ? new URL(Astro.site).origin : 'https://haseebstudio.com';
const lastUpdated = 'April 8, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Haseeb Studio Blog collects, uses, and shares information, including for Google AdSense."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold text-surface-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-surface-500 dark:text-surface-400 mb-10">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <div class="prose text-surface-700 dark:text-surface-300">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Haseeb Studio Blog</strong> (“we”, “us”) handles
        information when you visit <a href={siteOrigin}>{siteOrigin.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '')}</a>
        (the “Site”). By using the Site, you agree to this policy. If you do not agree, please do
        not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We may process the following types of information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage and technical data.</strong> Our hosting provider and infrastructure may log
          data such as your IP address, browser type, device type, referring URL, pages viewed, and
          timestamps. This helps operate, secure, and improve the Site.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies and similar technologies.</strong> We and our partners may use cookies,
          pixels, local storage, or similar technologies as described below.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you choose to send us.</strong> If you contact us by email or another
          channel, we receive whatever you provide (for example, your email address and message
          content).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Google AdSense and advertising</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to show advertisements on the Site. Google and its
        partners may use cookies and similar technologies to deliver and measure ads, including
        personalized ads based on your visits to this and other sites.
      </p>
      <p>
        Google’s use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on
        your visits to the Site and/or other websites on the Internet. You can learn more about how
        Google uses data when you use our partners’ sites or apps in
        <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          target="_blank"
          >Google’s Privacy &amp; Terms</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may opt out of <strong>personalized advertising</strong> by visiting
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
          >Google Ads Settings</a
        >. You can also visit
        <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
          >aboutads.info</a
        >
        for additional choices about interest-based ads from participating companies.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Hosting and service providers</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is hosted and delivered through third-party services (for example, hosting and
        deployment platforms). Those providers may process technical and log data on our behalf to
        serve pages and protect the service. Their use of data is governed by their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How we use information</h2>
      <p>We use the information described above to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the Site</li>
        <li>Measure traffic and understand how the Site is used</li>
        <li>Display and measure advertising (including through Google AdSense)</li>
        <li>Respond to inquiries and protect the security and integrity of the Site</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Legal bases (EEA, UK, and similar regions)</h2>
      <p>
        Where required by law, we rely on appropriate legal bases such as: your consent (for example,
        for certain cookies or ads where consent is required); our legitimate interests in running
        and improving the Site and keeping it secure; and compliance with legal obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only as long as needed for the purposes above or as required by law.
        Log and analytics-type data may be kept for a limited period according to our providers’
        settings and policies.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights and choices</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict
        certain processing of your personal data, or to object to processing or to data portability.
        You may also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. To exercise
        rights or ask questions, contact us using the details below. You can also use the ad opt-out
        tools linked in the AdSense section above.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 16 (or the minimum age in your jurisdiction). We
        do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have done so,
        please contact us and we will take appropriate steps.
      </p>

      <h2>9. International visitors</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may be accessed from countries other than where we operate. Your information may be
        processed in countries where our providers operate, which may have different data protection
        rules than your country.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version on this
        page and revise the “Last updated” date above. Continued use of the Site after changes means
        you accept the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
